PW: 6dN^dy$6)9O^TAr!

SoFi video link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YaeAYjpapX0
SMCC - AR link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xPV6kOadbvY


-Method 1:
    - Styling with HTML, CSS with Media query as follows:
    <style>
    .video-container {
        position: relative; 
        width: 75%;
    }
    .video-container .aspect-ratio {
        position: relative; 
        padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    } 
    @media (max-width: 1300px) {
    .video-container {
        width: 100%;
        }
    }
    </style>
    <center>
        <div class="video-container">
            <div class="aspect-ratio">
                <iframe 
                style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;"
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YaeAYjpapX0?si=ZLrV05x9QQJqNl0J" 
                title="YouTube video player" 
                frameborder="0" 
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
                allowfullscreen>
                </iframe>
            </div>
        </div>
    </center>

Pros: 
    -Adjustable in regards to dimensions.
    -Keeps the CM&D logo and video name visible on thumbnail.
    -A little bit better visual quality.

Cons:
    -Longer code to repeat.
    -Keeps the watch on YouTube and the red button are visible and take space on smaller screens

-Method 2:
    -Install Simple YouTube Responsive plug-in, activate and add a short code embed on the page with the following format:
    
    [youtube v=YaeAYjpapX0]

Pros:
    -One line of code.
    -Hides information on the thumbnail.

Cons:
    -Not adjustable (always 100vw)
    -A litte less visual quality.